Add
To
Compare
Why
We
Picked
It
It’s
likely
Mazda
took
its
highly
regarded
Mazda3,
lifted
it
by
2.4
inches
and
added
all-wheel
drive
to
the
menu
to
create
the
CX-30
compact
crossover.
The
CX-30
debuted
for
the
2020
model
year
and
slots
in
between
the
CX-3
and
the
CX-5
(it
also
splits
the
price
difference
of
the
two).
Its
sleek
looks
are
inspired
by
the
brand’s
“Kodo”
design
language
and
feel
fitting
enough
for
an
Italian-bred
crossover
despite
its
Japanese
heritage.
Its
interior
is
configured
smartly
for
its
footprint
and
it’s
clear
Mazda
designers
paid
more
attention
to
the
CX-30’s
hip
and
shoulder
room
than
the
older
CX-3,
which
is
burdened
by
a
jellybean
silhouette.
The
CX-30
boasts
