Why
We
Picked
It
The
Macan
compact
crossover
is
one
of
the
newest
members
of
the
Porsche
family
and
is
a
sporty
yet
practical
smaller
version
of
its
Cayenne
sibling.
The
best-seller
among
Porsches,
it
received
a
substantial
update
in
2019
and
was
reunited
with
the
Turbo
and
GTS
variants
for
the
2020
model
year.
The
base
Macan
has
a
turbocharged
248-horsepower
2.0-liter
inline-four
cylinder,
and
the
S
adds
an
extra
100
horsepower
from
a
3.0-liter
turbocharged
V6.
The
GTS
has
a
twin-turbo
2.9-liter
V6
that
delivers
375
horsepower
and
the
Turbo
brings
an
impressive
434
horsepower
from
its
twin-turbo
2.9-liter
V6.
Porsche’s
classical
styling
translates
well
on
the
larger
Macan,
but
the
highlight
is
that
the
crossover
doesn’t
compromise
much
in
terms
of
sportscar
handling.
Pros
&
Cons
Excellent
cabin
design
makes
efficient
use
of
cockpit
space
Three
variants
offer
wide
range
of
performance
options
Streamlined
design
and
ergonomics
make
for
exceptional
everyday
usability
Steep
pricing
and
skimpy
standard
equipment
list
Purists
might
find
four-cylinder
base
model
dull
Cargo
volume
takes
a
back
seat
to
sportiness
Specs
