transitioning
it
from
a
fuel-sipping
hatchback
to
a
daring
adventurer—it
has
8.4
inches
of
ground
clearance
and
all-wheel
drive
with
pre-set
modes
for
varying
terrain.
It
also
has
a
new
TRD
Off
Road
variant,
which
officially
includes
it
in
the
truck
family
to
which
the
rock-crawling
4Runner,
Tacoma,
Tundra
and
Sequoia
belong.
Toyota
also
added
a
plug-in
hybrid
model,
the
RAV4
Prime,
which
some
claim
is
indeed
the
“prime”
RAV4
to
buy.
With
so
many
configurations
available,
it’s
bound
to
please
a
wide
range
of
drivers.
